text: Auspicius may refer to one of several Catholic saints: *Auspicius of Apt, traditionally given as the first bishop of Apt, end of 1st century, said to have preserved the relics of Saint Anne *Auspicius of Toul, bishop of Toul at the end of the fifth century *Auspicius of Trier, Archbishop of Trier c. 131, who is perhaps to be identified with Auspicius of Toul
title: Auspicius
